DocumentDB has a similar looking (maybe not as powerful) interface:<p><pre><code>  context.collection.filter(function(doc) {
    return doc.city == &quot;Melbourne&quot; && doc.rating > 4.5;
  }).map(function(doc) {
    return doc.displayName;
  });</code></pre>

Rust also allows polymorphic return types.<p><pre><code>    trait Bounded {
        fn min_bound() -> Self;
        fn max_bound() -> Self;
    }
</code></pre>
Which can be used like so. Using type inference.<p><pre><code>    fn add_min_to_set<T:Bounded, S:MutableSet<T>>(set: &mut S) {
        set.insert(Bounded::min_bound())
    }
 </code></pre>
Or you can be more explicit<p><pre><code>    let mut i: u8 = Bounded::min_bound();
    while i < Bounded::max_bound() { println!(&quot;{}&quot;, i); i += 1; }
</code></pre>
